# Key Findings

The analysis revealed several important insights:

- Products placed at eye-level shelves achieved higher sales.
- Dairy and Snacks were the highest revenue-generating categories.
- Moderate discounts positively influenced sales volume.
- The South region recorded the highest revenue.
- Customers aged 25–40 years contributed the largest share of purchases.
- Supermarkets outperformed other store types in overall sales.
- Seasonal trends influenced monthly revenue.

---

# Business Recommendations

Based on the findings, the following recommendations are proposed:

- Place premium and fast-moving products at eye-level shelves.
- Maintain sufficient stock for high-demand categories.
- Offer strategic discounts to increase sales while preserving profitability.
- Focus marketing efforts on high-performing regions.
- Develop customer loyalty programs.
- Monitor KPIs regularly using Tableau dashboards.
- Improve inventory planning using sales trends.

